What if you do?

264
00:17:56,263 --> 00:18:00,100
I won't die until I spend
all the money you keep sending me.

265
00:18:00,184 --> 00:18:03,145
But you sent a lot this month.

266
00:18:03,896 --> 00:18:05,189
Why did you give me so much?

267
00:18:05,272 --> 00:18:07,316
Well, you're the owner of the business.

268
00:18:07,399 --> 00:18:08,609
It's only natural.

269
00:18:08,692 --> 00:18:10,986
Still, I'm just the figurehead.

270
00:18:11,069 --> 00:18:13,280
You're supposed to give
the figurehead a cut.

271
00:18:13,363 --> 00:18:14,573
It would be rude not to.

272
00:18:14,656 --> 00:18:17,409
Right. We shouldn't live like thugs.

273
00:18:17,492 --> 00:18:18,368
But…

274
00:18:19,786 --> 00:18:21,622
how long will you run that gambling den?

275
00:18:23,290 --> 00:18:25,584
It's not easy to manage it,
and it's dangerous.

276
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:28,712
Save what you're giving me
and help the others settle down.

277
00:18:28,795 --> 00:18:30,047
You make a clean break too.

278
00:18:30,130 --> 00:18:31,715
You've made enough money now.

279
00:18:31,798 --> 00:18:33,425
What are you talking about?

280
00:18:33,926 --> 00:18:37,095
After greasing everyone's palms,
there's nothing left.

281
00:18:37,179 --> 00:18:38,263
Plus,

282
00:18:38,764 --> 00:18:42,476
I have to earn a lot more
to help the guys follow their own paths.

283
00:18:42,559 --> 00:18:43,560
What about you?

284
00:18:44,686 --> 00:18:46,355
Is there anything you want to do?

285
00:18:47,064 --> 00:18:49,816
Gyeong-nam, Je-gil, and Big Guy.

286
00:18:50,442 --> 00:18:52,945
They all have dreams,
even if they may be small.

287
00:18:54,238 --> 00:18:55,280
Dreams?

288
00:18:57,824 --> 00:18:59,910
I don't have anything like that.

289
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:06,416
Make sure to take your meds.

290
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,170
You'd better not die on me. Or else I'll…

291
00:19:12,172 --> 00:19:13,465
-You little brat!
-Geez.

292
00:19:16,760 --> 00:19:17,761
You're still swift.

293
00:19:18,637 --> 00:19:19,930
Bring it on, you punk!

294
00:19:20,764 --> 00:19:22,432
I can't even see your hands.

295
00:19:22,516 --> 00:19:24,268
-You're too quick.
-Gosh…

296
00:19:25,978 --> 00:19:26,812
Let go of me!

297
00:19:26,895 --> 00:19:28,021
I'm not leaving.

298
00:19:28,105 --> 00:19:30,983
Lend me some money!

299
00:19:32,234 --> 00:19:34,111
Why can't you lend me money?

300
00:19:34,194 --> 00:19:36,321
Is his credit still top-tier?

301
00:19:36,405 --> 00:19:38,407
He's become our VVIP.

302
00:19:39,116 --> 00:19:40,033
Hang on.

303
00:19:40,659 --> 00:19:41,785
What?

304
00:19:41,868 --> 00:19:44,746
Mr. Park! Perfect timing.

305
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:47,040
These assholes…

306
00:19:47,124 --> 00:19:48,583
-They won't listen--
-Sir.

307
00:19:49,251 --> 00:19:51,128
When did you become our VVIP?

308
00:19:51,712 --> 00:19:52,963
Hurry up and lend it to him.

309
00:19:55,465 --> 00:19:56,508
I knew it.

310
00:19:56,591 --> 00:19:59,928
Things get done quickly
when I talk to the boss directly.

311
00:20:00,012 --> 00:20:01,263
Did you hear…

312
00:20:02,681 --> 00:20:04,975
You jerk. Why are you giving me that look?

313
00:20:05,058 --> 00:20:06,101
Hey.

314
00:20:06,184 --> 00:20:09,021
I can pay back everything
if I just work for a week

315
00:20:09,104 --> 00:20:10,564
at my apartment complex.

316
00:20:10,647 --> 00:20:12,733
Don't look down on me.

317
00:20:14,651 --> 00:20:15,819
-Lend him the money.
-Yes, sir.

318
00:20:15,902 --> 00:20:18,071
I'll see you again, sir.

319
00:20:19,531 --> 00:20:20,991
Thank you, Mr. Park.

320
00:20:21,074 --> 00:20:24,911
-I'll work really hard.
-Let's go.

321
00:20:24,995 --> 00:20:27,080
You're all dead!

322
00:20:27,164 --> 00:20:29,499
Just you wait! Let go of me.
Don't carry me…

323
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:31,335
Make sure we get
the money back right away.

324
00:20:31,418 --> 00:20:33,253
-I've got a bad feeling about this.
-Yes, sir.

325
00:20:40,052 --> 00:20:41,011
-Yun-seo.
-Yes?

326
00:20:41,094 --> 00:20:42,929
Is the representative election
notice ready?

327
00:20:43,013 --> 00:20:45,307
I'm just editing the text.
It's almost ready.

328
00:20:45,390 --> 00:20:46,266
-Okay.
-Right.

329
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:48,352
Don't put so much work into it.
Nobody cares.

330
00:20:50,062 --> 00:20:51,146
Sang-tae.

331
00:20:51,938 --> 00:20:55,817
Shouldn't we do our best to make sure
our residents pay more attention?

332
00:20:55,901 --> 00:20:57,778
We should make announcements every day.

333
00:20:57,861 --> 00:20:59,821
Right. Sorry.

334
00:21:09,998 --> 00:21:11,875
Ha-jeong.

335
00:21:13,335 --> 00:21:15,420
We'd like you to keep doing

336
00:21:15,504 --> 00:21:17,339
that job for us.

337
00:21:19,841 --> 00:21:21,676
I told you, I can't.

338
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:23,845
I said I'd stop when my sister got a job.

339
00:21:24,721 --> 00:21:25,972
Ha-jeong.

340
00:21:26,056 --> 00:21:29,101
Your sister's situation
is separate from yours.

341
00:21:30,268 --> 00:21:31,937
I'm sorry, sir.

342
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:33,480
I really can't keep doing it.

343
00:21:34,147 --> 00:21:37,609
I've told you many times
that you won't get in any trouble.

344
00:21:42,280 --> 00:21:45,242
Mr. Choi! Can you come out here for a bit?

345
00:21:45,325 --> 00:21:46,576
Mr. Choi.

346
00:21:46,660 --> 00:21:49,663
Can you please tell me what's going on?

347
00:21:49,746 --> 00:21:51,748
How can floor repairs

348
00:21:51,832 --> 00:21:53,500
cost 365 million…

349
00:21:53,583 --> 00:21:55,752
Oh my gosh. This is insane.

350
00:21:55,836 --> 00:21:58,130
Three hundred million won
is actually a bargain.

351
00:21:58,213 --> 00:21:59,673
Bargain or not,

352
00:21:59,756 --> 00:22:03,051
the construction company
should be taking care of this.

353
00:22:03,135 --> 00:22:05,470
Why would you repair this
with the residents' money?

354
00:22:05,554 --> 00:22:07,556
Who said you could use
the repair reserve fund?

355
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:10,600
This is exactly
what the repair reserve fund is for.

356
00:22:10,684 --> 00:22:15,105
You shouldn't spend it freely
just because it isn't your money.

357
00:22:15,188 --> 00:22:17,107
I'm so thirsty.
Give me something to drink.

358
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:19,192
It's not my money,

359
00:22:19,276 --> 00:22:22,070
but I'm spending it appropriately
for the right purposes.

360
00:22:22,154 --> 00:22:24,239
That's my job.

361
00:22:24,322 --> 00:22:25,532
Mr. Choi.

362
00:22:25,615 --> 00:22:27,993
When spending such a large amount,

363
00:22:28,076 --> 00:22:30,579
you should get
the residents' approval first.

364
00:22:30,662 --> 00:22:31,788
Well…

365
00:22:32,998 --> 00:22:34,332
This was an urgent matter.

366
00:22:34,416 --> 00:22:36,877
Urgent? Did the floors
crumble down or what?

367
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,170
Don't be ridiculous.

368
00:22:38,253 --> 00:22:39,754
Ms. Jang, you're so…

369
00:22:41,798 --> 00:22:44,050
invested in the complex's affairs.

370
00:22:44,801 --> 00:22:46,678
Of course, I am.

371
00:22:48,263 --> 00:22:49,306
Hello, everyone.

372
00:22:49,389 --> 00:22:50,640
You're here.

373
00:22:51,474 --> 00:22:53,226
-Hello.
-Hello.

374
00:22:53,727 --> 00:22:55,270
-Hello.
-Hello, sir.

375
00:22:55,353 --> 00:22:56,479
Hello.

376
00:22:56,563 --> 00:22:58,440
I received these as a gift,

377
00:22:58,523 --> 00:23:01,943
but I couldn't eat them all by myself,
so I thought I should share.

378
00:23:02,027 --> 00:23:04,196
Oh, you didn't have to. Thank you so much.

379
00:23:04,279 --> 00:23:05,113
Thank you.

380
00:23:06,823 --> 00:23:08,491
Thank you for always thinking of us.

381
00:23:08,575 --> 00:23:10,493
I'm just glad you all enjoy it.

382
00:23:10,577 --> 00:23:11,870
Let me get you some coffee.

383
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:14,748
It's fine. I was only dropping by.

384
00:23:14,831 --> 00:23:17,083
You must be busy. I'll get going now.

385
00:23:22,505 --> 00:23:23,465
You're quite the beauty.

386
00:23:26,051 --> 00:23:26,885
Oh my.

387
00:23:27,719 --> 00:23:29,596
-Me?
-Goodbye.

388
00:23:29,679 --> 00:23:31,348
-Goodbye.
-You heard that, right?

389
00:23:31,431 --> 00:23:33,308
He said I'm quite the beauty.

390
00:23:48,865 --> 00:23:51,201
PINE TREE FARM
TAEGOWON

391
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:08,426
Up we go.

392
00:24:16,726 --> 00:24:17,852
Goodness.

393
00:24:19,104 --> 00:24:20,480
-Hello.
-Hello.

394
00:24:20,563 --> 00:24:22,691
SENIOR SECRETARY FOR CIVIL AFFAIRS
SONG U-SIK

395
00:24:22,774 --> 00:24:24,693
PROSECUTOR GENERAL
CHOI SEUNG-HO

396
00:24:24,776 --> 00:24:25,902
How have you been?

397
00:24:25,986 --> 00:24:28,113
SUPREME COURT JUSTICE
YOO GWANG-HO

398
00:24:28,196 --> 00:24:29,739
PRESIDENT OF GONGYEONG DAILY
LEE SANG-GYU

399
00:24:37,622 --> 00:24:41,543
I sent Mr. Kim a bonsai tree.

400
00:24:42,377 --> 00:24:43,211
What?

401
00:24:43,295 --> 00:24:47,090
You already got Mr. Kim acquitted
and made him a presidential candidate.

402
00:24:47,173 --> 00:24:48,508
Why would you send him that?

403
00:24:48,591 --> 00:24:49,426
He's right.

404
00:24:50,051 --> 00:24:53,346
Our newspaper took plenty of heat
covering for Mr. Kim too.

405
00:24:53,430 --> 00:24:55,056
Just thinking about it makes me…

406
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:59,728
I just wanted him to see
the evergreen pine all year long

407
00:24:59,811 --> 00:25:00,729
and remember

408
00:25:01,313 --> 00:25:05,150
that we'll make him the president,
no matter what.

409
00:25:06,651 --> 00:25:10,655
Mr. Song, do you think
Mr. Kim really has a chance?

410
00:25:10,739 --> 00:25:13,491
Right now, he's the most likely candidate.

411
00:25:14,451 --> 00:25:16,536
"Most likely" isn't enough.

412
00:25:19,539 --> 00:25:22,167
We've spent a fortune on him so far.

413
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:25,337
We need him to win
the presidency this time

414
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,088
so it doesn't go to waste.

415
00:25:27,672 --> 00:25:30,300
And I'm certain
you'll all make sure that it happens.

416
00:25:32,135 --> 00:25:33,928
-Gosh.
-Of course.

417
00:25:34,012 --> 00:25:35,013
Thank you in advance.

418
00:25:35,096 --> 00:25:36,264
Of course.

419
00:25:57,243 --> 00:25:58,661
You're here.

420
00:25:59,537 --> 00:26:00,789
It wasn't hard to find, was it?

421
00:26:01,706 --> 00:26:02,749
Say hello.

422
00:26:03,416 --> 00:26:06,336
He's been eager to join our club.

423
00:26:06,836 --> 00:26:08,213
Nice to meet you.

424
00:26:08,713 --> 00:26:10,256
I'm Kwak Ju-gwon.

425
00:26:12,050 --> 00:26:13,510
-The police commissioner?
-Yes.

426
00:26:13,593 --> 00:26:18,556
He spent nearly 30 years
in public service, climbing the ranks.

427
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:20,767
I begged Mr. Song here

428
00:26:20,850 --> 00:26:23,645
to let me meet you all.

429
00:26:25,855 --> 00:26:27,232
Justice Yoo.

430
00:26:27,982 --> 00:26:30,318
Your rulings showed consideration
for the underprivileged

431
00:26:30,402 --> 00:26:32,570
and protected
the people's fundamental rights.

432
00:26:33,154 --> 00:26:35,198
I really admire you, sir.

433
00:26:37,325 --> 00:26:38,743
The president of Gongyeong Daily.

434
00:26:38,827 --> 00:26:40,829
You stood firm against media censorship.

435
00:26:41,454 --> 00:26:42,288
I truly admire you.

436
00:26:47,961 --> 00:26:51,381
And our Prosecutor General,
who led the charge for reform.

437
00:26:51,464 --> 00:26:53,383
You really are my role model…

438
00:26:53,466 --> 00:26:54,509
Hey, cop.

439
00:26:56,678 --> 00:26:58,263
Are you at a fan meet or what?

440
00:26:59,222 --> 00:27:00,056
Pardon?

441
00:27:00,140 --> 00:27:02,559
This isn't a social gathering.

442
00:27:03,435 --> 00:27:06,187
Didn't the Senior Secretary tell you that?

443
00:27:06,271 --> 00:27:08,231
I was going to…

444
00:27:19,367 --> 00:27:20,618
Look at that, huh?

445
00:27:21,286 --> 00:27:23,163
But not anyone can join us, you know.

446
00:27:23,788 --> 00:27:25,498
Yes, I know. That's why I--

447
00:27:25,582 --> 00:27:26,624
Ten billion!

448
00:27:29,586 --> 00:27:30,670
Do you have ten billion won?

449
00:27:30,753 --> 00:27:31,754
Excuse me?

450
00:27:31,838 --> 00:27:35,758
The people here
are worth more than ten billion won.

451
00:27:35,842 --> 00:27:37,719
If you want to join our One Club,

452
00:27:38,428 --> 00:27:39,512
bring ten billion

453
00:27:39,596 --> 00:27:40,805
for the membership fee.

454
00:27:41,306 --> 00:27:42,891
That's the least you can do.

455
00:27:44,642 --> 00:27:48,897
I've explained the membership requirement,
so please head back safely.

456
00:27:59,491 --> 00:28:00,408
Ten billion won?

457
00:28:07,582 --> 00:28:08,625
That's what he said.

458
00:28:09,626 --> 00:28:11,628
The membership fee is ten billion won.

459
00:28:11,711 --> 00:28:13,755
Ten billion for a membership?

460
00:28:15,381 --> 00:28:17,008
That makes no sense.

461
00:28:18,301 --> 00:28:20,845
Nothing makes sense in this country.

462
00:28:21,763 --> 00:28:24,140
If the most powerful people in Korea
want ten billion,

463
00:28:24,641 --> 00:28:25,600
then ten billion it is.

464
00:28:28,019 --> 00:28:29,187
What will you do then?

465
00:28:32,774 --> 00:28:36,986
You know that I didn't climb this high

466
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,196
by playing clean.

467
00:28:38,780 --> 00:28:40,365
I built a few connections

468
00:28:40,448 --> 00:28:43,117
and took some money.

469
00:28:44,702 --> 00:28:46,871
But thinking back now,

470
00:28:49,290 --> 00:28:52,210
I wonder if I should have been
even more corrupt.

471
00:28:53,503 --> 00:28:55,129
Even if I scrape together everything,

472
00:28:56,881 --> 00:28:58,341
it's hardly two billion.

473
00:28:58,842 --> 00:29:00,385
I need eight billion more.

474
00:29:00,468 --> 00:29:01,302
Sir.

475
00:29:05,682 --> 00:29:08,434
Why would you gather that money yourself?

476
00:29:10,103 --> 00:29:11,145
What?

477
00:29:13,481 --> 00:29:15,900
Squeeze it out of someone
who can't make a peep

478
00:29:15,984 --> 00:29:17,277
as you bleed them dry.

479
00:29:19,946 --> 00:29:21,906
That's impossible nowadays.

480
00:29:21,990 --> 00:29:23,616
There's someone perfect for that.

481
00:29:25,076 --> 00:29:28,580
Someone named Park Hae-kang,
who can do just about anything.

482
00:29:29,247 --> 00:29:30,456
Who is this guy?

483
00:29:31,666 --> 00:29:33,793
He runs a gambling den like a business.

484
00:29:33,877 --> 00:29:37,547
He's ruthless when it comes to making
and collecting money.

485
00:29:38,381 --> 00:29:39,215
Come in.

486
00:29:41,342 --> 00:29:43,469
Mr. Park, you have a visitor.

487
00:29:46,014 --> 00:29:47,140
Mr. Son.

488
00:29:47,223 --> 00:29:49,726
What's the occasion? You didn't call.

489
00:29:50,435 --> 00:29:52,770
Your office sure is nice, Mr. Park.

490
00:29:53,813 --> 00:29:55,440
You've succeeded.

491
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:58,943
Succeeded? I still have a long way to go.

492
00:30:01,029 --> 00:30:03,615
But what brings you here all of a sudden?

493
00:30:03,698 --> 00:30:05,867
I know you can pull off anything.

494
00:30:05,950 --> 00:30:08,578
At least, from what I've seen so far.

495
00:30:09,704 --> 00:30:11,748
-What is this about?
-Ten billion won.

496
00:30:12,832 --> 00:30:14,792
Get me ten billion won.

497
00:30:17,378 --> 00:30:18,212
Ten billion?

498
00:30:22,550 --> 00:30:24,260
What kind of scary joke is this?

499
00:30:27,055 --> 00:30:27,889
Sir.

500
00:30:28,765 --> 00:30:31,267
Have I done something wrong?

501
00:30:32,101 --> 00:30:33,978
If I have, please forgive me.

502
00:30:34,062 --> 00:30:36,022
-From now on--
-I'm not joking.

503
00:30:36,731 --> 00:30:38,608
Just think of it as paying it all up front

504
00:30:38,691 --> 00:30:41,235
instead of paying in installments
your whole life.

505
00:30:43,446 --> 00:30:47,241
How could I possibly have that much money?
Let alone in cash.

506
00:30:47,325 --> 00:30:48,368
Mr. Park.

507
00:30:49,702 --> 00:30:53,331
You've made a lot of money
with us watching your back.

508
00:30:53,414 --> 00:30:56,584
And I know how many customers you have.

509
00:30:56,668 --> 00:30:57,710
What's more,

510
00:31:00,046 --> 00:31:01,673
you're Park Hae-kang.

511
00:31:01,756 --> 00:31:03,257
You can make money out of thin air.

512
00:31:07,679 --> 00:31:11,099
I have nothing left
after greasing everyone's palms.

513
00:31:11,975 --> 00:31:15,561
I should clear things up
with you today, sir.

514
00:31:21,359 --> 00:31:22,819
Do I look like I'm joking right now?

515
00:31:26,572 --> 00:31:28,700
I can show you that I'm not joking.

516
00:31:29,409 --> 00:31:30,368
-Sir.
-Let go of me.

517
00:31:30,451 --> 00:31:31,995
-Sir…
-Let go!

518
00:31:33,746 --> 00:31:34,789
Mr. Son!

519
00:31:41,337 --> 00:31:43,464
What's going on, sir?

520
00:31:44,048 --> 00:31:45,216
He wants ten billion won.

521
00:31:45,717 --> 00:31:46,968
Ten billion won?

522
00:31:52,849 --> 00:31:54,642
Well, this isn't the first time.

523
00:31:55,476 --> 00:31:57,020
It's time to grease some palms.

524
00:31:57,103 --> 00:31:58,271
He must be short on money.

525
00:32:05,611 --> 00:32:06,654
The usual, right?

526
00:32:06,738 --> 00:32:08,239
Yes. Thank you.

527
00:32:08,948 --> 00:32:10,616
-Move aside, please!
-Move!

528
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:12,285
Excuse me.

529
00:32:13,536 --> 00:32:15,705
I'm an employee here!

530
00:32:15,788 --> 00:32:17,457
I'm telling you, it's my first time here!

531
00:32:17,540 --> 00:32:18,875
Please proceed quietly!

532
00:32:18,958 --> 00:32:19,876
Here's your coffee.

533
00:32:19,959 --> 00:32:21,544
I'm calling my lawyer!

534
00:32:21,627 --> 00:32:23,254
Let go of me!

535
00:32:25,006 --> 00:32:26,883
I just followed someone here!

536
00:32:38,311 --> 00:32:39,145
Please pick up.

537
00:32:39,228 --> 00:32:40,646
MR. SON, SEOUL POLICE CHIEF

538
00:32:48,488 --> 00:32:49,447
This is crazy.

539
00:32:50,364 --> 00:32:51,282
I can't believe this.

540
00:32:52,408 --> 00:32:53,785
Hold on.

541
00:32:53,868 --> 00:32:54,911
What's with him?

542
00:32:54,994 --> 00:32:56,913
Geez.

543
00:32:56,996 --> 00:32:58,539
This place was a gambling den?

544
00:32:58,623 --> 00:33:02,043
Apparently, only people
with top-tier credit ratings got in.

545
00:33:02,627 --> 00:33:05,004
I'll call you back in a minute, sweetie.

546
00:33:05,088 --> 00:33:06,130
Okay.

547
00:33:06,756 --> 00:33:08,007
Are you okay? That jerk!

548
00:33:08,091 --> 00:33:09,467
He hit me!

549
00:33:09,550 --> 00:33:10,760
-Why'd you hit me?
-Are you okay?

550
00:33:11,344 --> 00:33:12,720
-He's beating me up!
-What?

551
00:33:12,804 --> 00:33:14,305
A thug hit me! Call the cops!

552
00:33:14,388 --> 00:33:15,264
-Call the cops!
-Cops!

553
00:33:15,348 --> 00:33:17,225
When did I hit you? I…

554
00:33:17,308 --> 00:33:19,560
-What's going on?
-A thug hit me!

555
00:33:20,311 --> 00:33:21,938
-He's obviously a thug.
-No, I…

556
00:33:22,021 --> 00:33:24,649
All right. I tripped while I was walking…

557
00:33:29,821 --> 00:33:32,573
Sir, you're under arrest for assault.

558
00:33:32,657 --> 00:33:35,868
You have the right to remain silent,
and you have the right to an attorney.

559
00:33:35,952 --> 00:33:38,037
MR. PARK HAE-KANG

560
00:33:45,461 --> 00:33:47,255
We're conducting a Breathalyzer test.

561
00:33:48,673 --> 00:33:50,466
It's 0.09. Your license will be revoked.

562
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:51,717
-What?
-Please step out.

563
00:33:55,054 --> 00:33:56,556
But I didn't drink!

564
00:33:56,639 --> 00:33:58,099
I can't drink at all.

565
00:33:58,182 --> 00:33:59,517
I can't drink a drop of alcohol.

566
00:33:59,600 --> 00:34:01,310
MR. PARK HAE-KANG

567
00:34:01,394 --> 00:34:02,353
Get in there.

568
00:34:02,436 --> 00:34:03,271
Wait.

569
00:34:04,188 --> 00:34:05,606
Sir, wait.

570
00:34:05,690 --> 00:34:07,650
Why am I in here?

571
00:34:07,733 --> 00:34:10,153
You were reported
for illegally filming women's bodies.

572
00:34:10,236 --> 00:34:12,864
What? Hang on. Illegal filming?

573
00:34:12,947 --> 00:34:15,449
My phone is right here. Look.

574
00:34:15,533 --> 00:34:17,118
All I have are photos of bread!

575
00:34:17,201 --> 00:34:18,744
MR. PARK HAE-KANG

576
00:34:18,828 --> 00:34:19,787
Here. Look.

577
00:34:19,871 --> 00:34:21,372
That's my phone. Wait…

578
00:34:21,455 --> 00:34:22,582
Give it back!

579
00:34:23,166 --> 00:34:24,750
About that issue…

580
00:34:24,834 --> 00:34:27,170
Mr. Park Yong-man
of HK Trading and Investment?

581
00:34:29,297 --> 00:34:30,256
What's this about?

582
00:34:30,339 --> 00:34:31,674
ARREST WARRANT

583
00:34:31,757 --> 00:34:32,758
You need to come with us.

584
00:34:38,598 --> 00:34:42,351
We raided the gambling den,
so we have to bring in the figurehead.

585
00:34:43,144 --> 00:34:44,770
Don't take it too personally.

586
00:35:28,856 --> 00:35:30,942
I've brought everything I could.

587
00:35:45,456 --> 00:35:48,459
I'll take this in return
for releasing your men.

588
00:35:49,043 --> 00:35:51,003
You'll need them to get your work done.

589
00:35:51,629 --> 00:35:52,672
I'll give you three months

590
00:35:53,881 --> 00:35:55,383
for the ten billion I mentioned.

591
00:35:55,925 --> 00:35:57,593
Bring it to me in three months.

592
00:35:58,177 --> 00:35:59,303
And Yong-man?

593
00:36:05,768 --> 00:36:07,520
I need to have some insurance too.

594
00:36:08,229 --> 00:36:11,274
I'll exchange Park Yong-man
for the ten billion.

595
00:36:24,036 --> 00:36:27,915
OUTSTANDING ATHLETE AWARD
PARK HAE-KANG

596
00:36:27,999 --> 00:36:30,501
SPORTS AWARD
PARK HAE-KANG

597
00:36:30,584 --> 00:36:33,921
DAEJUN HIGH SCHOOL
PARK HAE-KANG

598
00:36:40,136 --> 00:36:41,178
Who is it?

599
00:36:45,891 --> 00:36:48,019
What are you doing
in someone else's house?

600
00:36:55,943 --> 00:36:57,153
You must be

601
00:36:57,820 --> 00:36:59,280
Park Hae-kang.

602
00:36:59,989 --> 00:37:00,906
Who are you?

603
00:37:08,122 --> 00:37:09,373
This…

604
00:37:10,666 --> 00:37:14,879
is the loan agreement your father signed
to borrow 30 million won from me.

605
00:37:15,755 --> 00:37:18,007
And you, Park Hae-kang,
are the collateral.

606
00:37:20,176 --> 00:37:21,844
Where is he?

607
00:37:36,067 --> 00:37:37,318
Yes!

608
00:37:37,902 --> 00:37:39,153
What the hell?

609
00:37:39,236 --> 00:37:40,071
What?

610
00:37:40,988 --> 00:37:43,240
You crushed my dream,
and now you're selling me too?

611
00:37:43,324 --> 00:37:44,450
How can you do that to me?

612
00:37:44,533 --> 00:37:45,659
What kind of father are you?

613
00:37:45,743 --> 00:37:48,120
What are you waiting for? Kick him out!

614
00:37:48,204 --> 00:37:51,123
You should manage your business properly!

615
00:37:51,207 --> 00:37:52,500
You little brat!

616
00:37:52,583 --> 00:37:53,709
And he calls himself my son?

617
00:37:53,793 --> 00:37:56,003
How can a father do this to his own child?

618
00:37:56,087 --> 00:37:56,921
Let go of me!

619
00:37:57,004 --> 00:37:58,130
Let go!

620
00:38:00,341 --> 00:38:02,093
Leave while we're asking nicely.

621
00:38:44,510 --> 00:38:45,845
Are you done crying?

622
00:38:50,099 --> 00:38:53,561
I can't do the "I'm your father" thing,

623
00:38:54,437 --> 00:38:58,899
but you can work for me
until you piece your broken dream

624
00:38:59,859 --> 00:39:00,943
back together.

625
00:39:02,736 --> 00:39:03,863
Park Hae-kang.

626
00:39:17,793 --> 00:39:20,254
The food here is amazing.

627
00:39:20,337 --> 00:39:22,840
Perfectly balanced meals…

628
00:39:22,923 --> 00:39:24,341
Just hang in there.

629
00:39:24,842 --> 00:39:26,135
I'll get you out soon.

630
00:39:26,218 --> 00:39:28,804
It's fine. Take your time.

631
00:39:29,555 --> 00:39:31,140
It's not my first time here.

632
00:39:31,849 --> 00:39:33,184
It feels like my old hometown.

633
00:39:39,523 --> 00:39:42,526
Hae-kang, don't strain yourself too hard
to get me out.

634
00:39:43,110 --> 00:39:45,738
I don't have much longer to live anyway.

635
00:39:45,821 --> 00:39:49,575
Find a way to save the others.
They're all relying on you.

636
00:39:51,076 --> 00:39:52,786
Cut the nonsense.

637
00:39:52,870 --> 00:39:56,373
Ever since I took you under my wing
20 years ago,

638
00:39:56,457 --> 00:39:59,293
you've already been
a good enough son to me.

639
00:39:59,960 --> 00:40:03,088
So stop taking care
of other people's lives

640
00:40:03,631 --> 00:40:05,174
and focus on your own.

641
00:40:18,521 --> 00:40:19,355
No.

642
00:40:19,855 --> 00:40:21,273
Don't be ridiculous.

643
00:40:32,952 --> 00:40:34,995
You all went through a lot.

644
00:40:37,790 --> 00:40:38,666
Mr. Park.

645
00:40:40,209 --> 00:40:42,169
Are we just supposed to
take this lying down?

646
00:40:43,379 --> 00:40:45,589
We have enough dirt on Mr. Son too.

647
00:40:46,173 --> 00:40:49,510
It'll be more than enough
to take him down.

648
00:40:50,094 --> 00:40:52,012
He won't stop at Yong-man.

649
00:40:52,638 --> 00:40:53,973
He got to you guys too.

650
00:40:54,056 --> 00:40:56,725
He can easily destroy your lives.

651
00:40:56,809 --> 00:40:58,435
Still, it's ten billion.

652
00:41:00,271 --> 00:41:01,897
Where would we get ten billion won?

653
00:41:02,398 --> 00:41:04,775
We've been extorted
out of over one billion won so far.

654
00:41:04,858 --> 00:41:07,027
But ten billion?

655
00:41:07,611 --> 00:41:09,154
Go live your own lives now.

656
00:41:11,782 --> 00:41:13,659
I'll take care of this.

657
00:41:14,243 --> 00:41:16,120
We're not some gang anyway.

658
00:41:16,787 --> 00:41:18,581
And I'm not your gang leader.

659
00:41:19,164 --> 00:41:20,666
I'm just the CEO,

660
00:41:21,542 --> 00:41:23,002
and you're the employees.

661
00:41:24,128 --> 00:41:25,504
Think of this as quitting.

662
00:41:25,588 --> 00:41:26,630
I'll give you

663
00:41:28,257 --> 00:41:30,009
your severance pay later.

664
00:41:33,053 --> 00:41:34,346
What about our old boss?

665
00:41:35,180 --> 00:41:36,265
What will you do?

666
00:41:37,349 --> 00:41:38,601
He's like a father to me.

667
00:41:39,101 --> 00:41:40,185
I'll take care of him.

668
00:41:42,813 --> 00:41:43,647
Go.

669
00:41:51,196 --> 00:41:52,323
Guys.

670
00:41:54,366 --> 00:41:56,452
Are you sure it's okay to just leave?

671
00:42:07,546 --> 00:42:08,380
Go on.

672
00:42:09,048 --> 00:42:10,007
I'll get going.

673
00:42:11,508 --> 00:42:12,760
Bye. I'll call you.

674
00:42:14,011 --> 00:42:15,012
What are you waiting for?

675
00:42:15,846 --> 00:42:16,847
Bye.

676
00:42:16,930 --> 00:42:18,140
Wait.

677
00:42:22,478 --> 00:42:23,604
Guys.

678
00:42:25,022 --> 00:42:26,273
I'll see you again later.

679
00:42:29,652 --> 00:42:33,614
CHEERS TO YONG-MAN'S NEW BEGINNING!

680
00:42:45,167 --> 00:42:46,043
Sir.

681
00:42:50,422 --> 00:42:51,757
I'm not going to quit.

682
00:42:57,137 --> 00:42:58,055
I won't quit.

683
00:43:00,057 --> 00:43:00,891
Sir…

684
00:43:03,227 --> 00:43:04,186
I…

685
00:43:05,562 --> 00:43:06,772
I'm not quitting either.

686
00:43:07,564 --> 00:43:08,482
What's with you guys?

687
00:43:09,733 --> 00:43:10,984
When Gyeong-buk…

688
00:43:12,986 --> 00:43:14,947
was just an infant,

689
00:43:15,030 --> 00:43:17,908
our boss would change his diapers
and read to him.

690
00:43:18,492 --> 00:43:19,868
He practically raised him.

691
00:43:20,494 --> 00:43:22,204
I couldn't graduate from law school,

692
00:43:22,287 --> 00:43:24,248
but he was the one who secretly paid

693
00:43:24,331 --> 00:43:25,541
for my tuition.

694
00:43:27,126 --> 00:43:29,002
He always praised my cooking

695
00:43:29,086 --> 00:43:30,879
and said I had incredible talent.

696
00:43:30,963 --> 00:43:33,924
He even said
people would line up to try my food

697
00:43:34,007 --> 00:43:35,384
if I opened a restaurant.

698
00:43:35,467 --> 00:43:38,303
He's the one who helped me find my dream.

699
00:43:44,143 --> 00:43:45,102
Mr. Park,

700
00:43:46,687 --> 00:43:47,980
let us help you

701
00:43:49,148 --> 00:43:50,733
save our old boss.

702
00:43:50,816 --> 00:43:52,818
We're not a gang now,

703
00:43:52,901 --> 00:43:55,779
but we're more than just
a CEO and staff, aren't we?

704
00:43:56,780 --> 00:43:57,781
He's right.

705
00:43:58,282 --> 00:44:00,743
We live together, and we die together.

706
00:44:01,243 --> 00:44:02,661
Let us help you!

707
00:44:05,914 --> 00:44:07,666
Are you sure you won't regret it?

708
00:44:08,250 --> 00:44:09,543
-Yes.
-Yes.

709
00:44:14,089 --> 00:44:15,257
Then let's do this.

710
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:18,594
Ten billion.

711
00:44:19,178 --> 00:44:20,846
I'm sure we'll find a way.

712
00:44:32,065 --> 00:44:35,068
A double-eyelid surgery is quite simple,

713
00:44:35,152 --> 00:44:36,570
so there's no need to be nervous.

714
00:44:36,653 --> 00:44:38,530
Dr. Han, if you don't pay me back,

715
00:44:38,614 --> 00:44:40,449
you might end up
under permanent anesthesia.

716
00:44:41,909 --> 00:44:42,743
COURTHOUSE

717
00:44:42,826 --> 00:44:44,203
Mr. Prosecutor, sir!

718
00:44:44,286 --> 00:44:47,456
The defendant today
was up for habitual illegal gambling.

719
00:44:47,539 --> 00:44:50,959
Can I sue someone for not paying back
their illegal gambling funds?

720
00:44:51,752 --> 00:44:54,630
Why has it been so difficult to reach you?

721
00:44:54,713 --> 00:44:55,964
YOON JEONG-BOK

722
00:44:56,882 --> 00:44:58,342
You'd better pay up now.

723
00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:02,012
Hello. It's been a while, sir.

724
00:45:02,095 --> 00:45:03,180
Hello.

725
00:45:03,263 --> 00:45:04,473
But who…

726
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:10,354
Hi there.

727
00:45:14,983 --> 00:45:16,944
This is True Value.

728
00:45:17,027 --> 00:45:19,112
At this price, you got a great deal.

729
00:45:22,157 --> 00:45:25,410
We collected unpaid debts
and even sold my car and apartment,

730
00:45:25,494 --> 00:45:26,954
but this is all we got?

731
00:45:27,538 --> 00:45:29,206
Geez.

732
00:45:31,542 --> 00:45:33,126
A 1st birthday party two weeks ago,

733
00:45:33,210 --> 00:45:37,172
and now Man-sik is having
his 60th birthday party next month.

734
00:45:37,256 --> 00:45:39,758
Who celebrates
their 60th birthday these days?

735
00:45:39,841 --> 00:45:42,261
I know everyone collects money
after retiring, but that jerk…

736
00:45:42,344 --> 00:45:44,221
I mean, he's taken
over 100 million from us.

737
00:45:44,304 --> 00:45:45,305
Hang on.

738
00:45:45,973 --> 00:45:49,393
It was his kid's 1st birthday,
and he's turning 60 next month?

739
00:45:50,060 --> 00:45:51,520
He had a kid at 59 years old?

740
00:45:52,688 --> 00:45:54,147
Did you hear anything

741
00:45:54,231 --> 00:45:56,358
about how much he collected
at the birthday party?

742
00:45:56,441 --> 00:45:57,526
I'm not sure how much,

743
00:45:57,609 --> 00:46:00,529
but I heard he bought an apartment
after the party.

744
00:46:00,612 --> 00:46:02,197
An apartment? Where?

745
00:46:02,281 --> 00:46:04,074
-In Gangnam?
-Yes.

746
00:46:07,202 --> 00:46:08,495
We should host something too.

747
00:46:09,288 --> 00:46:11,999
-Host something?
-We've been giving out money.

748
00:46:12,082 --> 00:46:13,542
I bet it's at least 600 million.

749
00:46:13,625 --> 00:46:15,002
We'll gain it all back this time.

750
00:46:15,711 --> 00:46:16,795
What kind of event?

751
00:46:17,379 --> 00:46:18,380
A wedding!

752
00:46:18,463 --> 00:46:20,966
Wouldn't weddings bring in
the most cash gifts?

753
00:46:21,049 --> 00:46:22,467
That's a good idea.

754
00:46:22,551 --> 00:46:24,553
But we don't have a bride.

755
00:46:26,263 --> 00:46:27,723
How may I help you, ma'am?

756
00:46:31,476 --> 00:46:33,937
WEE PARTNERS
FREE LEGAL CONSULTATION APPLICATION

757
00:46:34,021 --> 00:46:36,565
My son's dead.

758
00:46:37,774 --> 00:46:39,359
People keep telling me

759
00:46:39,443 --> 00:46:42,988
I have to renounce the inheritance
or something,

760
00:46:43,071 --> 00:46:45,741
but I don't have the money
to hire a lawyer.

761
00:46:47,159 --> 00:46:48,619
You came to the right place.

762
00:46:48,702 --> 00:46:51,371
We're here to help people like you.

763
00:46:53,248 --> 00:46:55,417
-You filed the death report, right?
-Yes.

764
00:46:56,001 --> 00:46:57,711
Take these files.

765
00:46:58,962 --> 00:47:00,631
Thank you so much.

766
00:47:00,714 --> 00:47:02,591
Of course. I get paid to do this.

767
00:47:05,344 --> 00:47:06,219
Ms. Kang.

768
00:47:06,970 --> 00:47:07,888
Yes?

769
00:47:08,847 --> 00:47:09,681
Well…

770
00:47:10,515 --> 00:47:13,310
Don't you know we send up customers
for cases like that?

771
00:47:13,810 --> 00:47:16,396
It should've been a paid case.

772
00:47:18,315 --> 00:47:19,274
YEONG-JU

773
00:47:19,358 --> 00:47:22,152
She didn't have much money.

774
00:47:24,196 --> 00:47:26,198
You're unbelievable.

775
00:47:33,246 --> 00:47:35,332
-What?
-Are you free this weekend?

776
00:47:35,415 --> 00:47:36,416
There's a gig for you.

777
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:39,586
-What is it?
-Can you afford to be picky right now?

778
00:47:39,670 --> 00:47:41,254
You need to send money to your sister.

779
00:47:43,632 --> 00:47:44,508
Deal.

780
00:47:50,138 --> 00:47:52,140
WARMEST CONGRATULATIONS
ON YOUR BEAUTIFUL UNION

781
00:47:52,724 --> 00:47:53,975
-Hello!
-Hello!

782
00:47:56,311 --> 00:47:58,355
-I'm here.
-Hey.

783
00:48:03,902 --> 00:48:05,362
He's here.

784
00:48:06,988 --> 00:48:07,823
Wow.

785
00:48:07,906 --> 00:48:09,991
Am I in a crime movie or what?

786
00:48:10,075 --> 00:48:11,535
Who's getting married?

787
00:48:12,411 --> 00:48:13,870
WE'RE GETTING MARRIED

788
00:48:13,954 --> 00:48:15,038
GROOM
PARK HAE-KANG

789
00:48:15,122 --> 00:48:16,415
PARK HAE-KANG & KIM MIN-JI

790
00:48:16,498 --> 00:48:17,874
CONGRATULATIONS, HAE-KANG

791
00:48:17,958 --> 00:48:20,877
YOUR BROTHER, TADAYOSHI

792
00:48:22,754 --> 00:48:23,630
Boss!

793
00:48:34,349 --> 00:48:36,017
-Move over for a bit.
-What?

794
00:48:37,185 --> 00:48:38,437
Do I have to go this far?

795
00:48:40,564 --> 00:48:42,232
One of you can do it. Why me?

796
00:48:44,025 --> 00:48:45,110
We already told you.

797
00:48:45,193 --> 00:48:47,112
We'll get more cash if you're the groom.

798
00:48:47,195 --> 00:48:48,530
Wow.

799
00:48:48,613 --> 00:48:49,614
You look so handsome.

800
00:48:49,698 --> 00:48:50,741
Your lips are very nice.

801
00:48:50,824 --> 00:48:53,452
He's the most handsome customer
you've had, isn't he?

802
00:48:53,535 --> 00:48:54,494
See?

803
00:48:55,704 --> 00:48:56,705
Mr. Park!

804
00:48:57,998 --> 00:49:01,168
All our retired members are here.

805
00:49:01,251 --> 00:49:03,754
The venue's filled with guests!

806
00:49:03,837 --> 00:49:06,131
But we're already out of beef tartare.

807
00:49:09,092 --> 00:49:10,719
Is the bride here?

808
00:49:16,099 --> 00:49:16,933
Me?

809
00:49:17,601 --> 00:49:19,102
I'm getting married today?

810
00:49:19,186 --> 00:49:21,021
That's what I'm telling you.

811
00:49:21,104 --> 00:49:22,564
Hurry up and change.

812
00:49:22,647 --> 00:49:24,149
You need to get your makeup done.

813
00:49:24,649 --> 00:49:26,902
There must be some kind of mistake.

814
00:49:26,985 --> 00:49:28,820
I thought I was going to be a guest.

815
00:49:28,904 --> 00:49:30,822
I'm sorry. I can't do this.

816
00:49:30,906 --> 00:49:33,033
I heard you were referred by Yeong-ju.

817
00:49:33,116 --> 00:49:34,659
You can't back out now.

818
00:49:34,743 --> 00:49:37,496
How would we find
another bride last-minute?

819
00:49:39,331 --> 00:49:41,958
-I'll pay you generously.
-Ma'am.

820
00:49:42,042 --> 00:49:45,545
Didn't you see those men out there?
They look like thugs.

821
00:49:45,629 --> 00:49:48,632
The groom must be someone
in the underworld.

822
00:49:49,424 --> 00:49:50,342
I'm sorry.

823
00:49:51,927 --> 00:49:54,513
Hey, you can't just leave now!

824
00:49:54,596 --> 00:49:56,264
We don't have time.

825
00:49:58,558 --> 00:49:59,851
Five million won.

826
00:50:05,065 --> 00:50:06,066
Deal.

827
00:50:18,161 --> 00:50:20,747
The wedding of Park Hae-kang

828
00:50:20,831 --> 00:50:22,374
and Kim Min-ji will begin shortly…

829
00:50:22,457 --> 00:50:25,585
I know this must be overwhelming,
but I'm counting on you.

830
00:50:27,754 --> 00:50:30,423
In any case, let's do this.

831
00:50:33,969 --> 00:50:35,095
Hold on tight.

832
00:50:35,178 --> 00:50:36,805
…let us meet the bride and groom.

833
00:50:36,888 --> 00:50:39,307
Please welcome them
with a big round of applause.

834
00:50:40,100 --> 00:50:42,394
The bride and groom will now enter.

835
00:51:12,340 --> 00:51:14,843
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

836
00:51:14,926 --> 00:51:18,221
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

837
00:51:18,305 --> 00:51:20,849
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

838
00:51:20,932 --> 00:51:24,102
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

839
00:51:24,185 --> 00:51:27,355
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

840
00:51:27,439 --> 00:51:30,275
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

841
00:51:40,702 --> 00:51:43,580
Sharing a life as husband and wife

842
00:51:45,332 --> 00:51:49,753
is not easy, of course,

843
00:51:49,836 --> 00:51:51,504
but if you live as each other's half

844
00:51:51,588 --> 00:51:54,507
and live faithfully together,

845
00:51:55,091 --> 00:51:56,051
you'll…

846
00:51:59,512 --> 00:52:00,764
Live happily together.

847
00:52:07,854 --> 00:52:12,317
Next, to celebrate this joyful union,

848
00:52:12,400 --> 00:52:15,362
the groom's colleagues have prepared

849
00:52:15,445 --> 00:52:17,113
a special performance.

850
00:52:17,781 --> 00:52:19,658
Please welcome them
with a round of applause.

851
00:52:24,788 --> 00:52:28,833
We're going to smile, smile again

852
00:52:28,917 --> 00:52:32,253
This is a happy moment, happy day

853
00:52:32,337 --> 00:52:34,464
Straighten your shoulders

854
00:52:34,547 --> 00:52:39,302
And erase all your worries

855
00:52:39,386 --> 00:52:42,597
Forget your sadness, never cry

856
00:52:42,681 --> 00:52:45,809
Beneath the blazing sun, sunny day

857
00:52:46,393 --> 00:52:50,271
Just wish for only good things

858
00:52:50,355 --> 00:52:52,482
To come your way

859
00:53:00,240 --> 00:53:04,035
Like the vast sky, laugh louder

860
00:53:04,119 --> 00:53:07,539
And think bigger

861
00:53:07,622 --> 00:53:10,750
Forget your tears, never cry

862
00:53:10,834 --> 00:53:13,712
Like the bright sunlight, sunshine day

863
00:53:13,795 --> 00:53:19,592
I'll pray that your days
Will be filled with happiness

864
00:53:19,676 --> 00:53:20,885
Park Hae-kang!

865
00:53:20,969 --> 00:53:22,846
Congratulations, Park Hae-kang!

866
00:53:22,929 --> 00:53:24,723
Picture-perfect, Park Hae-kang!

867
00:53:32,188 --> 00:53:33,898
All right.

868
00:53:33,982 --> 00:53:36,735
Then lastly, why don't the bride and groom

869
00:53:36,818 --> 00:53:38,778
kiss for the photo?

870
00:53:43,616 --> 00:53:47,746
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

871
00:53:47,829 --> 00:53:49,622
Mr. Park, you have to kiss!

872
00:53:49,706 --> 00:53:53,376
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

873
00:53:53,460 --> 00:53:56,963
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

874
00:53:57,047 --> 00:54:00,133
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

875
00:54:00,216 --> 00:54:01,760
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

876
00:54:01,843 --> 00:54:03,178
Two million more.

877
00:54:03,261 --> 00:54:07,307
-Kiss! Kiss!
-Kiss! Kiss!

878
00:54:29,954 --> 00:54:30,830
It's okay.

879
00:54:31,998 --> 00:54:33,291
I got paid more.

880
00:54:34,250 --> 00:54:35,251
So it's fine.

881
00:54:50,975 --> 00:54:52,477
Is it the right amount?

882
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:54,729
Two million extra for the kiss.

883
00:54:54,813 --> 00:54:56,189
Yes. Everything's in there.

884
00:54:56,272 --> 00:54:59,234
But it wasn't a proper kiss.

885
00:54:59,859 --> 00:55:00,693
What?

886
00:55:00,777 --> 00:55:02,070
The kiss.

887
00:55:02,153 --> 00:55:05,698
I only kissed my thumb,
and it was next to your lips.

888
00:55:12,372 --> 00:55:14,624
Still, we touched.

889
00:55:14,707 --> 00:55:16,501
Do you even know how I feel?

890
00:55:17,001 --> 00:55:18,002
I paid a fair, I mean…

891
00:55:18,586 --> 00:55:21,881
I paid you plenty for that.
Should I worry about your feelings too?

892
00:55:21,965 --> 00:55:25,301
You hired a fake bride
and held a grand wedding.

893
00:55:25,385 --> 00:55:27,303
I feel like I'm involved
in some huge scam.

894
00:55:27,387 --> 00:55:29,139
It just feels wrong.

895
00:55:29,222 --> 00:55:31,266
What's more, there's this…

896
00:55:31,349 --> 00:55:32,934
There was some touching involved.

897
00:55:33,017 --> 00:55:35,145
Well, you were the one who said,

898
00:55:35,228 --> 00:55:38,481
"Deal."

899
00:55:38,565 --> 00:55:40,608
You said it so willingly.

900
00:55:41,901 --> 00:55:42,819
Anyway,

901
00:55:43,361 --> 00:55:46,489
this was unpleasant for both of us,
so let's not cross paths again.

902
00:55:51,327 --> 00:55:53,788
As someone working in law,
let me tell you something.

903
00:55:53,872 --> 00:55:56,457
Stay on the right side of the law.

904
00:56:05,466 --> 00:56:07,427
Let's just focus on helping Yong-man.

905
00:56:08,511 --> 00:56:09,429
Focus.

906
00:56:13,099 --> 00:56:14,392
We're still 6.5 billion short.

907
00:56:14,475 --> 00:56:15,810
Is there anything else?

908
00:56:15,894 --> 00:56:18,479
There's only the Lizard
to collect from, but…

909
00:56:18,563 --> 00:56:20,481
Luck is on my side today.

910
00:56:20,565 --> 00:56:21,399
Thanks.

911
00:56:22,233 --> 00:56:24,736
-But what?
-I visited his management office,

912
00:56:24,819 --> 00:56:26,279
but they said he's currently wanted.

913
00:56:26,779 --> 00:56:27,947
Wanted? For what?

914
00:56:28,031 --> 00:56:29,616
Embezzlement and breach of trust.

915
00:56:30,450 --> 00:56:32,243
Find him before the police do.

916
00:56:32,327 --> 00:56:34,913
Tell him to pay me back
with the money he embezzled.

917
00:56:35,705 --> 00:56:36,998
I just got the Lizard's location.

918
00:56:39,209 --> 00:56:40,251
He's in Osan.

919
00:56:40,835 --> 00:56:42,337
Get him. Now.

920
00:56:57,936 --> 00:56:59,646
I'll pay you back! Please!

921
00:56:59,729 --> 00:57:01,189
Please don't kill me!

922
00:57:06,569 --> 00:57:08,154
Mr. Park is here.

923
00:57:08,238 --> 00:57:09,572
Sir!

924
00:57:09,656 --> 00:57:10,949
Mr. Park!

925
00:57:11,032 --> 00:57:12,992
What took you so long?

926
00:57:13,076 --> 00:57:14,661
Tell them to let me go.

927
00:57:14,744 --> 00:57:16,120
I'm freezing right now.

928
00:57:16,204 --> 00:57:18,331
-Please, help me!
-What about my money?

929
00:57:18,414 --> 00:57:20,917
We retrieved 20 million,
and we checked his credit rating.

930
00:57:21,000 --> 00:57:22,252
It's Grade 8.

931
00:57:22,335 --> 00:57:23,795
Then he can't pay me back.

932
00:57:30,760 --> 00:57:32,345
You assholes!

933
00:57:32,428 --> 00:57:34,264
Are you a bunch of thugs or what?

934
00:57:34,931 --> 00:57:38,810
You're just lowlifes earning petty cash
from a gambling den!

935
00:57:38,893 --> 00:57:40,478
You can't kill anyone!

936
00:57:40,562 --> 00:57:42,272
Come on, then! Kill me!

937
00:57:42,855 --> 00:57:44,649
Get on with it! I'm freezing!

938
00:57:44,732 --> 00:57:47,318
-I'll either freeze to death or fall!
-Level 2!

939
00:57:47,402 --> 00:57:48,319
Just try…

940
00:57:50,572 --> 00:57:51,864
Help me!

941
00:57:51,948 --> 00:57:53,533
Help me! I'm sorry!

942
00:57:53,616 --> 00:57:54,951
I'm sorry!

943
00:57:55,994 --> 00:57:57,078
I'm sorry.

944
00:57:57,954 --> 00:58:00,331
I won't act up, I swear.

945
00:58:15,221 --> 00:58:16,097
Mr. Park.

946
00:58:17,098 --> 00:58:18,683
Are there about 10,000 households here?

947
00:58:22,103 --> 00:58:23,062
What?

948
00:58:23,563 --> 00:58:25,315
This apartment complex!

949
00:58:26,858 --> 00:58:28,484
Are there about 10,000 households?

950
00:58:29,444 --> 00:58:30,570
There are 9,800.

951
00:58:35,491 --> 00:58:37,327
I saw on my way here

952
00:58:37,410 --> 00:58:40,788
that your apartment complex is having
a building representative election.

953
00:58:40,872 --> 00:58:42,665
I have a great idea.

954
00:58:42,749 --> 00:58:43,750
Just hear me out.

955
00:58:43,833 --> 00:58:44,834
Get rid of him.

956
00:58:44,917 --> 00:58:47,795
-Just throw him off. Let's go.
-Wait!

957
00:58:47,879 --> 00:58:49,589
There's easy money

958
00:58:50,089 --> 00:58:53,134
in this apartment complex
that you don't know about!

959
00:58:54,594 --> 00:58:56,012
Check my jacket.

960
00:58:56,095 --> 00:58:58,890
There's a notebook
and some account books in my pocket.

961
00:58:58,973 --> 00:59:00,600
You'll believe me once you see it.

962
00:59:20,036 --> 00:59:20,870
Let him go for now.

963
00:59:22,038 --> 00:59:23,081
Thank you.

964
00:59:26,000 --> 00:59:27,543
It's the other way.

965
00:59:32,507 --> 00:59:35,510
Isn't this going a bit too far
for a prank?

966
00:59:36,427 --> 00:59:37,720
What is this?

967
00:59:42,183 --> 00:59:44,352
Records of what I've been skimming off.

968
00:59:44,894 --> 00:59:48,064
I inflated the maintenance fees
and procurement costs

969
00:59:48,648 --> 00:59:51,109
and received payments
from bidding competitors.

970
00:59:52,985 --> 00:59:54,737
I gambled with money from all that.

971
00:59:55,321 --> 00:59:57,240
So this is proof that you're trash…

972
00:59:58,533 --> 01:00:01,327
I can pay back everything
if I just work for a week

973
01:00:01,411 --> 01:00:03,037
at my apartment complex.

974
01:00:06,040 --> 01:00:07,125
PLUMBING MATERIALS

975
01:00:07,208 --> 01:00:08,376
ELECTRICAL SUPPLIES

976
01:00:08,459 --> 01:00:09,419
CHRISTMAS EVENT

977
01:00:09,502 --> 01:00:10,503
EXTERIOR WALL CONSTRUCTION

978
01:00:10,586 --> 01:00:12,213
MAINTENANCE FEES, SECURITY SERVICE…

979
01:00:15,216 --> 01:00:16,300
SENIOR CENTER REMODELING

980
01:00:16,384 --> 01:00:18,219
SUPPLIES ORGANIZATION, LANDSCAPING…

981
01:00:19,804 --> 01:00:20,680
Four billion?

982
01:00:22,682 --> 01:00:24,517
You pocketed four billion won?

983
01:00:25,101 --> 01:00:27,103
Our apartment complex
only has 1,200 households,

984
01:00:27,687 --> 01:00:29,439
and I skimmed that much.

985
01:00:29,522 --> 01:00:30,440
But this place

986
01:00:30,940 --> 01:00:34,068
has almost 10,000 households.

987
01:00:34,152 --> 01:00:36,946
Then how much do you think
you can skim off?

988
01:00:37,655 --> 01:00:39,323
A billion? Two billion?

989
01:00:39,407 --> 01:00:41,826
That's pocket change!

990
01:00:42,410 --> 01:00:44,120
You could even skim off ten billion!

991
01:00:47,248 --> 01:00:49,542
I'm serious, Mr. Park!

992
01:00:50,251 --> 01:00:51,210
Ten billion?

993
01:00:51,294 --> 01:00:52,295
Yes.

994
01:01:26,204 --> 01:01:27,622
We can skim off

995
01:01:29,081 --> 01:01:30,374
ten billion won

996
01:01:31,167 --> 01:01:32,668
from this apartment complex?

997
01:01:38,508 --> 01:01:40,426
THE APARTMENT JOB

998
01:02:04,575 --> 01:02:06,702
How do we skim off ten billion then?

999
01:02:06,786 --> 01:02:10,039
Become the building representative,
then the president.

1000
01:02:10,122 --> 01:02:11,666
Would there really be ten billion here?

1001
01:02:11,749 --> 01:02:14,377
Ask them how much
the long-term repair reserve fund is.

1002
01:02:14,460 --> 01:02:15,294
Long-term what?

1003
01:02:15,378 --> 01:02:18,297
There's 17,857,420,000 won.

1004
01:02:18,381 --> 01:02:19,799
The complex residents
aren't doing anything?

1005
01:02:19,882 --> 01:02:23,302
Everyone's busy with their own lives.
They don't even care about it.

1006
01:02:23,386 --> 01:02:25,346
-You have to run for building rep.
-Do you live alone?

1007
01:02:25,429 --> 01:02:28,015
I've never seen anyone living alone
run for building representative.

1008
01:02:28,099 --> 01:02:30,977
We need a family
to take that repair reserve fund.

1009
01:02:31,060 --> 01:02:32,770
Mom, Dad, Grandma, Grandpa.
People like that.

1010
01:02:32,854 --> 01:02:34,063
Let's work on something together.

1011
01:02:34,146 --> 01:02:35,857
Play the role of my wife for three months.

1012
01:02:35,940 --> 01:02:37,775
-Play the role of what?
-My wife.

1013
01:02:37,859 --> 01:02:38,776
A hundred million.

1014
01:02:38,860 --> 01:02:40,486
A hundred million for three months.

1015
01:02:43,614 --> 01:02:45,616
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

